  "prompt": "How do I get 95%+ in Class 12th Boards? What reference books can I use for it?",
  "response": "Scoring 95%+ in Class 12th Boards requires a strategic approach, dedication, and consistent effort. Here are some tips and reference books that can help you achieve your goal:\n\n### Tips for Scoring High:\n\n1. **Understand the Syllabus:** Get a thorough understanding of the CBSE syllabus and exam pattern. Focus on the chapters and topics that have higher weightage.\n\n2. **Plan Your Study Schedule:** Create a realistic and organized study schedule. Allocate time for each subject and ensure you have enough time for revision.\n\n3. **Conceptual Clarity:** Focus on understanding concepts rather than rote memorization. This will help you tackle application-based questions effectively.\n\n4. **Practice Regularly:** Solve previous years' question papers, sample papers, and mock tests to get a feel of the actual exam. Time yourself to improve speed and accuracy.\n\n5. **Revision:** Regular revision is crucial. Make summary notes and highlight important points. Use flashcards for quick revision.\n\n6. **Focus on Weak Areas:** Identify your weak areas and work on them diligently. Seek help from teachers or peers if necessary.\n\n7. **Health & Sleep:** Maintain a balanced diet, exercise regularly, and ensure you get adequate sleep. A healthy body supports a healthy mind.\n\n### Reference Books:\n\n**English:**\n1. **Hornbill** (for CBSE Class 12)\n2. **Snapshots** (for CBSE Class 12)\n3. **BBC Compacta** for English \u2013 It offers a variety of exercises and sample papers.\n\n**Mathematics:**\n1. **NCERT Books** \u2013 The cornerstone for board preparation.\n2. **RD Sharma** \u2013 Detailed explanation and variety of problems for practice.\n3. **RS Aggarwal** \u2013 Good for additional practice.\n\n**Physics:**\n1. **NCERT Textbooks** \u2013 Fundamental concepts and theory.\n2. **Concepts of Physics by H.C. Verma** \u2013 Good for conceptual understanding and numerical practice.\n3. **Pradeep's Fundamental Physics** \u2013 In-depth explanations and solved examples.\n\n**Chemistry:**\n1. **NCERT Textbooks** \u2013 Comprehensive coverage of the syllabus.\n2. **Modern\u2019s ABC of Chemistry** \u2013 Detailed approach and practice problems.\n3. **Op Tandon** \u2013 Good for both organic and inorganic chemistry.\n\n**Biology:**\n1. **NCERT Textbooks** \u2013 Precise and well-structured content.\n2. **Pradeep\u2019s Biology** \u2013 Detailed concepts and additional questions.\n3. **Trueman\u2019s Elementary Biology** \u2013 Good for comprehensive practice.\n\n**Economics:**\n1. **NCERT Textbooks** \u2013 Basic understanding and essential concepts.\n2. **S. Chand\u2019s Economics** \u2013 In-depth explanation of concepts.\n3. **T.R. Jain and V.K. Ohri** \u2013 Additional practice and application-based questions.\n\n### Additional Resources:\n\n1. **Sample Papers:** Obtain sample papers from Oswaal, Arihant, or other trusted publishers for practice.\n2. **Online Resources:** Websites like Meritnation, TopperLearning, and Byju\u2019s offer free and paid content for deeper understanding.\n\nRemember that consistency, practice, and staying calm under pressure are key to achieving high marks in your board exams.",
